    <title type="html"><![CDATA[你想在头上插根棍子么？]]></title>
    <link href="http://pikipity.github.com/blog/bmi.html"/>
    <updated>2013-07-19T20:15:00+08:00</updated>
    <id>http://pikipity.github.com/blog/bmi</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>本来看到万老师实验的脑电研究，还幻想过用脑电控制机械手臂什么的，但是看完《Brain–machine interfaces: past, present and future》之后我知道了，用这些待在头上的帽子只能测量低频率的脑电波，还没法精确测量，拼写个单词也就是极限了。看了介绍非插入式一段最后总结的一句话后，就彻底桑心了：</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>But if the goal of a BMI is to restore movements with multiple degrees of freedom through the control of an artificial prosthesis, the message from published evidence is clear: this task will require recording of highresolution signals from the brain, and this can be done using invasive approaches.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>但是谁愿意像下面这样在脑袋上插根棍子啊，急需志愿者。</p>

